      • solve

        public final java.util.Iterator<AStar.State> solve(Ilayout s,
                                                   Ilayout goal)
        Uses the A* algorithm to find the most low cost path from 's' to 'goal' All problems that can be solved using A* can be solved with this method as long as it implements correctly the Ilayout interface and it contains a good heuristic for that specific problem
        Parameters:
        s - initial configuration
        goal - the desired configuration at end of path
        Returns:
        an iterator with the sequence of configuration from 's' to 'goal'
